HEADWORD: layby
<hw>layby</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>A paved area beside a main road where
cars can stop temporarily.</def> <mark>[Chiefly Brit.]</mark> ⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> pull-off, turnout.</syn>⟦br⟧
